    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - TROUBLESHOOTING - SHAFT FITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SHAFT FITS</title>
        <para>Bearing fits on rotating shafts are usually specified as tight. Excessive looseness-even .001 "-under a
            load produces a creeping or slipping of the inner race on the rotating shaft. The result is that surface
            metal of the shafts scrub or wear off. The force causing the inner race to rotate disappears when the
            bearing fits properly.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
